parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive fuel vapor emission can lead to a fire hazard, explosions, and health risks due to inhalation of toxic fumes. It can also cause discomfort and inconvenience to riders and those nearby.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline or fuel fumes
especially after riding on warm or hot days
liquid condensation from the fuel tank vent
and overheating of the fuel tank and exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine overheating without warning
stalling
engine smoke
fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Engine Compartment Venting and Exhaust System Isolation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor engine compartment venting and exhaust system isolation can cause extreme heat to build up under the seat and leg area, making the ride uncomfortable and potentially dangerous.
symptoms: Excessive heat generated under the seat and leg area
especially on the right side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause strong gasoline odors, which can be a fire hazard and create an unpleasant riding experience.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odors
especially after parking the vehicle
overwhelming fuel fumes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
electronic throttle control warning lamp illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including faulty instrument clusters, horn malfunctions, and false codes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument cluster malfunctions
the horn shorts out and requires frequent fuse replacement
the shock compressor turns on and off randomly
and the vehicle throws out numerous codes and false codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fires, which can lead to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire around the fuel cap area
and there are reports of vapor leaks or fuel line leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starting system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start after stopping
and it takes multiple attempts to start the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal switch can cause hazardous situations, as the driver's attention is diverted from the road to verify that the signal has been properly canceled.
symptoms: The turn signal switch does not cancel properly
causing the left signal to flash when canceling a right turn
and the left signal begins to flash as if it was pressed to signal a left turn.
